The paper explores the use of physical keyboards in virtual reality and investigates how to fully leverage the immersiveness of VR to change the input and output characteristics of physical keyboard interaction within a VR environment. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Virtual Reality (cs.VR) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the design and implementation of various applications, such as text processing macros and a photo browser, which suggests that it may also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), and Cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-categories.
